outputs.output_descr:
The primary objective of the project is to build the capacity of non-state actors to advocate for and enforce rights related to access to quality HIV/AIDS prevention, treatment, care and support services for vulnerable populations and those who need them the most. It will benefit seven countries in the region  Armenia, Azerbaijan, Belarus, Georgia, Moldova, Ukraine and the Russian Federation  with specific country-level pilot activities in Moldova, the Russian Federation and Ukraine.
This project looks to:
-	strengthen the advocacy skills of non-state actors to lobby effectively for improved access to HIV/AIDS prevention, treatment, care and support, especially for people living with HIV, adolescents and vulnerable groups such as women, prisoners, migrant workers, men having sex with men (MSM), sex workers and injecting drug users;
-	support actions enhancing the quality of services provided by non-state actors and public sector and the integration of prevention, treatment and care services;
-	support actions strengthening partnerships and coordination among non-state actors and with public bodies, develop regional ownership strategies and facilitate the exchange of lessons learned and good practice in HIV/AIDS prevention, treatments and care.
